            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "RCHEM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " ADDITION OF NB CARRIER TO MO SAMPLE FOLLOWED BY",
                " DISSOLUTION IN ACID. THE NB WAS PRECIPITATED BY NEU-",
                " TRALISING THE SOLUTION WITH NH4OH, AND THEN HEATED TO",
                " TO FORM THE OXIDE WHICH WAS TRANSFERRED TO AN AL",
                " PLANCHET FOR X-RAY COUNTING. CHEMICAL YIELD DETERMINED",
                " GRAVIMETRICALLY AND ALSO FROM FAST NEUTRON ACTIVATION",
                " ANALYSIS SEVERAL MONTHS LATER USING 93-NB(N,2N)92-NB-M"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".EITHER MO POWDER IN A POLYTHENE CAPSULE (DIAM 1.2 CM,",
                " LENGTH 1.3 CM) OR A STACK OF MO FOILS (DIAM 1.6 CM,",
                " HEIGHT 0.8 CM). IN BOTH CASES THE MO WAS 99.9% PURE.",
                " AL MONITOR FOILS OF THE SAME SIZE WERE ATTACHED TO THE",
                " FRONT AND BACK OF THE SAMPLE. IN GENERAL THE FLUX",
                " DENSITY WAS 4.0E+7 N/CM2/S."
